  1. Create a histogram for each defensive statistic. Use facet_wrap to draw all histograms in a single plot. What defensive skills are rare?
ggplot(defClean, aes(x=Statistic))+geom_histogram(binwidth = 1)+facet_wrap(~Type) + ylab("Number of Players")+ggtitle("Relationship between Number of players and Statistic")

Conclusion: From the plot, it shows that Turnover_FR and Turnover_INT skills are most rare.

  1. Did ISU have better defense against West Virginia or Kansas State? Answer this question by creating a scatterplot with x-axis being the number of solo tackles (by each player) against West Virginia, and y-axis being that against Kansas State. A large number of solo tackles indicates good defense.
TwoState <- defense %>% 
  filter(Opponent == 'West Virginia'| Opponent == 'Kansas State') %>%
  select(Name, Opponent, Tackles_Solo) %>%
  spread(key=Opponent, value=Tackles_Solo)
TwoState
